net.sf.jclec.mo.evaluation

Class MOEvaluator

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.base.AbstractEvaluator
      • net.sf.jclec.mo.evaluation.MOEvaluator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.IEvaluator, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC, IMOEvaluator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DTLZ1Evaluator, DTLZ2Evaluator, DTLZ3Evaluator, DTLZ4Evaluator, DTLZ5Evaluator, DTLZ6Evaluator, DTLZ7Evaluator, MOKnapsackEvaluator, MOTSPEvaluator

    public class MOEvaluator
extends net.sf.jclec.base.AbstractEvaluator
implements IMOEvaluator
    Evaluator for a multi-objective problem. It evaluates each solution using a list of configured objectives. Solutions are evaluated sequentially.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    AbstractEvaluator, IMOEvaluator, Objective, Serialized Form

      • configure

        public void configure(org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration settings)

        Parameters for MOEvaluator are:

        • objectives (List of Objective): The list of objectives to be evaluated. Parameters for every objective (using the tag "objective") are:
          • [@type] (String): Path to class that implements the objective.
          • [@min] (double): Minimum value, negative infinite by default.
          • [@max] (double): Maximum value, positive infinite by default.
          • [@maximize] (boolean): The objective should be maximized (true) or minimized (false).

        Specified by:
        configure in interface net.sf.jclec.IConfigure
